JIRA: 6.3.11

Modify {{UnreviewedCodeCondition}} to make it ignore changesets which haven't been reviewed, but don't any revisions (didn't change anything).

Package: com.atlassian.jirafisheyeplugin.domain.workflow.condition;

Please add in "try" block this simple code:

{code:java}
				if (cs.getRevisionCount() == 0) {
					continue;
				}
{code}

Full class:


{code:java}
package com.atlassian.jirafisheyeplugin.domain.workflow.condition;

import com.atlassian.jira.ComponentManager;
import com.atlassian.jira.issue.Issue;
import com.atlassian.jira.workflow.condition.AbstractJiraCondition;
import com.atlassian.jirafisheyeplugin.domain.crucible.Review;
import com.atlassian.jirafisheyeplugin.domain.crucible.ReviewManager;
import com.atlassian.jirafisheyeplugin.domain.fisheye.ChangeSetManager;
import com.atlassian.jirafisheyeplugin.domain.fisheye.ChangeSets;
import com.atlassian.jirafisheyeplugin.domain.fisheye.Changeset;
import com.opensymphony.module.propertyset.PropertySet;
import org.slf4j.Logger;
import org.slf4j.LoggerFactory;

import java.io.IOException;
import java.util.Iterator;
import java.util.List;
import java.util.Map;

public class UnreviewedCodeCondition extends AbstractJiraCondition {

    private static final Logger log = LoggerFactory.getLogger(UnreviewedCodeCondition.class);

    public boolean passesCondition(Map transientVars, Map args, PropertySet ps) {
        Issue issue = (Issue) transientVars.get(ORIGINAL_ISSUE_KEY);

        ChangeSets changesets = getChangeSetManager().getChangesetsForIssue(issue);
        ReviewManager reviewManager = getReviewManager();
        for (Changeset cs : changesets.getChangesets()) {
            try {
				if (cs.getRevisionCount() == 0) {
					continue;
				}
				
                List<Review> revs;
                if (cs.isReviewsInitialised()) {
                    revs = cs.getReviews();
                } else {
                    revs = reviewManager.getReviewsForChangeset(issue.getProjectObject().getKey(), cs.getCsid(), cs.getRep());
                }
                if (revs.isEmpty()) {
                    //unreviewed code!
                    return false;
                }
            } catch (IOException e) {
                log.error("Error retrieving reviews for UnreviewedCodeCondition (csid: " + cs.getCsid() + "):", e);
            }
        }

        return true;
    }

    //Overrideable for tests
    protected ReviewManager getReviewManager() {
        return ComponentManager.getOSGiComponentInstanceOfType(ReviewManager.class);
    }

    //Overrideable for tests
    protected ChangeSetManager getChangeSetManager() {
        return ComponentManager.getOSGiComponentInstanceOfType(ChangeSetManager.class);
    }

}
{code}

Currently there's logic in insertFileRevision which creates parent dirs for path if those don't exists. 
{code}
        if (startRevWithNoImport) {
            // if a start revision is set with "no import" we might not have all the paths in the repository, so make sure all the parent dirs exist
            createParentDirs(path);
        }
{code}

It makes no sense especially for branch creation commit. We store Paths in HashMap, which make cause during iterating over it some path with a created file comes before path with parent dir path causing premature dir creation. Later on when Fisheye is processing Path connected with that particular dir it checks if it already exists and ignore it if it does. 


Note affect only configuration with Start Revision and No Import settings.

h3. Problem Definition
The list of committers for a repository cannot be retrieved via REST API.

h3. Suggested Solution
Provide a REST API call to retrieve the list of committers for a specific repository.

h3. Workaround
The list of committers for a repository can be displayed in the FishEye user interface by hitting the following URL:
{noformat}
<FISHEYE_URL>/users/<repository_name>
{noformat}

The page displayed by the following URL can be used to retrieve the Top Committers for a repository:
{noformat}
<FISHEYE_URL>/plugins/servlet/code-metrics/<repository_name>
{noformat}

